Massachusetts Climate Projections for specific decadesÂ¶

In [480]:
import ma_eea as ma
from ipy_table import *
%matplotlib inline

#from IPython.core.interactiveshell import InteractiveShell
#InteractiveShell.ast_node_interactivity = "all"

Climate change projections for every variable are:

  • relative to the baseline period of 1971-2000.
  • based on 30-year means centered on 2030s, 2050s, 2070s. Projections for 2090s are based on 20-year means (2080-2099) since model simulations are available only until 2100.
  • based on 28 total projections - 2 RCP scenarios (RCP4.5, RCP8.5) for 14 CMIP5 climate models each.
  • presented as 10th, 25th, 75th, 90th percentile values across 28 projections.
    -- 10th Percentile --> Low Estimate
    -- 25th-75th Percentile --> Middle Range
    -- 90th Percentile --> High Estimate
